---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import EmailCapture from '../components/EmailCapture.astro';
---

<Base
  title="48-Hour Healthcare Market Research Reports"
  activePage="products"
  description="Analyst-grade healthcare and clinical research market reports delivered in 48 hours. Flat $750 fee. Written by a practitioner working on FDA-regulated studies at a 21-hospital US academic health system."
>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <div class="product-top">
    <div class="product-hero">
      <div class="product-hero-text">
        <span class="product-badge">Research Service</span>
        <h1>Healthcare Market Research, Delivered in 48 Hours</h1>
        <p class="product-tagline">
          You need to understand your market. You don't need a $15,000 agency and a three-week wait.
          Written by a practitioner working on FDA-regulated studies at a 21-hospital US academic
          health system. Structured, cited, analyst-grade reports in healthcare, life sciences,
          and clinical operations — turned around in 48 hours.
        </p>
        <div class="product-price-row">
          <span class="product-price">$750</span>
          <span class="product-price-note">flat fee · no revisions theater · delivered as PDF</span>
        </div>
        <a href="/buy/research-report?utm_source=direct&utm_medium=research-report-hero" class="buy-btn">Order a Report</a>
        <p class="buy-note">
          Secure checkout via Stripe. After payment, you'll receive an intake form and a link to schedule a 15-minute scoping call (optional).
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="product-hero-preview">
        <div>
          <p style="margin: 0 0 0.5rem; font-weight: 600; text-align: center;">Read a Free Sample</p>
          <p style="margin: 0 0 1rem; font-size: 0.9rem; opacity: 0.85;">
            <em>What FDA Inspections Have Been Finding at US Oncology Trial Sites</em> —
            a 1-page public sample with primary-source citations. See the depth before you buy.
          </p>
          <p style="margin: 0; text-align: center;">
            <a href="/sample-report/">Read the sample &rarr;</a>
          </p>
          <p style="margin: 0.75rem 0 0; text-align: center; font-size: 0.85rem; opacity: 0.75;">
            or see <a href="/healthcare-market-research-pricing/">how this compares</a> to other research firms
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="product-stats">
      <div class="stat"><strong>48 hrs</strong> Turnaround</div>
      <div class="stat-sep"></div>
      <div class="stat"><strong>20-30</strong> Pages</div>
      <div class="stat-sep"></div>
      <div class="stat"><strong>Cited</strong> Sources</div>
      <div class="stat-sep"></div>
      <div class="stat"><strong>Healthcare</strong> Focus</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- What You Get -->
  <section class="why-now-section">
    <h2>What You Get</h2>
    <div class="why-now-grid">
      <div class="why-now-card">
        <h3>Executive Summary</h3>
        <p>The one-page version you send to your board, co-founder, or investor. Key findings, bottom-line recommendation, and the data that supports it. No filler.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="why-now-card">
        <h3>Market Landscape</h3>
        <p>Size, growth rate, regulatory context, reimbursement environment (where applicable), and the forces that are actually moving the category right now. Written in plain language, not consulting-speak.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="why-now-card">
        <h3>Competitor Matrix</h3>
        <p>Direct and adjacent competitors mapped against the dimensions your decision actually depends on. Pricing, positioning, feature gaps, and recent moves that matter.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="why-now-card">
        <h3>Buyer Personas</h3>
        <p>Who actually signs the check. What their day-to-day pain is. What language they respond to. What they already use and why they'd switch.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="why-now-card">
        <h3>Regulatory & Compliance Context</h3>
        <p>If your market touches FDA, EMA, HIPAA, 21 CFR Part 11, ICH-GCP, or any life-sciences regulation — these are documents Tyrian reads for a living. This section is the reason you're hiring a clinical professional instead of a generalist.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="why-now-card">
        <h3>Sourced Citations</h3>
        <p>Every claim is cited. Primary sources where possible. You can hand the report to a skeptical CFO, lawyer, or investor and they can verify any number themselves.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How It Works -->
  <section class="why-now-section">
    <h2>How It Works</h2>
    <div class="why-now-grid">
      <div class="why-now-card">
        <h3>1. You Order</h3>
        <p>Pay the flat $750 fee. Fill out a short intake form describing your market, your decision, and any specific questions you need answered. Optional 15-minute scoping call if the brief needs clarification.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="why-now-card">
        <h3>2. Research Delivered Overnight</h3>
        <p>Deep research using AI-augmented workflows and primary-source verification. This is what makes $750 feasible for work that would take a traditional consultant 40 hours. You get the analyst output; the AI is in the basement, not the deliverable.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="why-now-card">
        <h3>3. You Get the Report</h3>
        <p>Within 48 hours of your intake submission, you receive a structured 20-30 page PDF in your inbox. One round of clarification questions included. No revision spiral — the report is the product.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Why Me -->
  <section class="why-now-section">
    <h2>Why This Is Different From Generic Market Research</h2>
    <div class="why-now-grid">
      <div class="why-now-card">
        <h3>Practitioner-Level Clinical Research Background</h3>
        <p>Tyrian Murex is a clinical research associate at a 21-hospital US academic health system, working on active FDA-regulated studies. When a report covers clinical trials, site operations, CRO dynamics, regulatory pathways, or reimbursement — that isn't research done for the first time. It's the day job.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="why-now-card">
        <h3>ICH-GCP Certification and Hands-On Regulatory Context</h3>
        <p>FDA guidance documents, ICH E6(R3), 21 CFR Parts 11/50/56/312, and EMA publications are part of normal work. If your market research touches regulated workflows, you're getting context a generalist freelancer would have to Google.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="why-now-card">
        <h3>AI-Augmented Engineering, Human Judgment</h3>
        <p>AI handles the heavy retrieval and first-pass drafting. Tyrian applies the judgment, verifies the claims, and structures the narrative. You pay for the judgment layer — which is the layer that costs $750 instead of $15,000.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="why-now-card">
        <h3>No Revision Theater</h3>
        <p>The flat fee includes one clarification round for genuinely unclear asks. It doesn't include endless scope creep, "can you also look at…" additions, or rewriting the tone twice. If you need a different angle, that's a new report. This keeps the service fast and the price honest.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Use Cases -->
  <section class="why-now-section">
    <h2>When This Is the Right Service</h2>
    <div class="why-now-grid">
      <div class="why-now-card">
        <h3>Founders Evaluating a Healthcare or Life-Sciences Market</h3>
        <p>You're deciding whether to enter a category. You need real data, not vibes — and you need it before your next board meeting.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="why-now-card">
        <h3>Operators Preparing for a Funding Round</h3>
        <p>You need a defensible market analysis for an investor deck or data room. One your analysts can verify and your CFO can defend.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="why-now-card">
        <h3>Teams Doing Competitive Due Diligence</h3>
        <p>You need to understand a specific competitor's positioning, pricing, or regulatory posture before your next strategic decision.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="why-now-card">
        <h3>Consultants Needing Overflow Research Capacity</h3>
        <p>Your client asked for something you don't have time to research yourself. Subcontract the research to someone who can turn it around in 48 hours and knows the clinical space.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="why-now-section">
    <h2>FAQ</h2>
    <div class="why-now-grid">
      <div class="why-now-card">
        <h3>Is $750 really the full price?</h3>
        <p>Yes. Flat fee. Payment is taken at order. The only reason it might be more is if your scope is larger than one report — in which case I'll tell you before you pay, not after.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="why-now-card">
        <h3>What if I need non-healthcare research?</h3>
        <p>I focus on healthcare, life sciences, and clinical operations because that's where my credentials create real value. If your brief is adjacent (health-tech, medical device, digital health, pharma ops, CRO services), yes. If your brief is a crypto project or a SaaS horizontal, no — there are better-fit freelancers for that.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="why-now-card">
        <h3>Can I see a sample report?</h3>
        <p>Yes. <a href="/sample-report">Read our public 1-page sample</a> — a pattern read of FDA Form 483 observations at US oncology trial sites (2023–2025) with primary-source citations. It shows the analytical depth and citation discipline a full report delivers.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="why-now-card">
        <h3>What if it's not useful?</h3>
        <p>If the report materially fails the brief — meaning the scope we agreed on in the intake wasn't delivered — I'll rework it or refund. That's not the same as "I wanted a different conclusion," which is a scope disagreement, not a quality issue.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="why-now-card">
        <h3>Do you sign NDAs?</h3>
        <p>Yes. Mutual NDA available on request before intake. All client information stays confidential — your research is not reused for other clients.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="why-now-card">
        <h3>Can I talk to you first?</h3>
        <p>Yes. The order button kicks off a 15-minute scoping call option before I start the research. If you'd rather talk first, book a call directly: <a href="https://calendly.com/nexrial/healthcare-market-research-scoping-call">schedule a call</a>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Final CTA -->
  <section class="why-now-section" style="text-align: center;">
    <div style="max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <h2>Ready to Order?</h2>
      <p style="max-width: 640px; margin: 0 auto 1.5rem;">
        $750 flat. 48 hours. Healthcare and life-sciences market research written by a practitioner living in the regulated world.
      </p>
      <a href="/buy/research-report?utm_source=direct&utm_medium=research-report-cta" class="buy-btn" style="display: inline-block;">Order a Report</a>
      <p class="buy-note" style="margin-top: 1rem;">
        Or <a href="https://calendly.com/nexrial/healthcare-market-research-scoping-call">book a 15-minute call</a> first.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Lead magnet + email capture -->
  <section class="why-now-section">
    <div style="padding: var(--spacing-lg); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px; background: var(--purple-glow); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);">
      <p style="font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: var(--purple-primary); margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0;">Free to read first</p>
      <h3 style="font-size: 1.1rem; margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0;">FY2022–2024 BIMO 483 Observation Taxonomy</h3>
      <p style="margin: 0 0 1rem 0; color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 0.95rem; max-width: 720px;">
        See the depth standard before you commission a custom report. Seven observation categories, verified primary-source citations, FDA BIMO base rates. Free, no signup.
      </p>
      <a href="/bimo-taxonomy/" class="buy-btn" style="max-width: 260px;">Read the Taxonomy &rarr;</a>
    </div>
    <EmailCapture
      heading="Or follow the practitioner notes"
      subheading="Monthly notes from a practitioner working in FDA-regulated oncology studies. No pitch — just specific, cited observations from the inside of clinical research operations."
    />
  </section>

  <!-- Service Terms — future-proofing baseline -->
  <section class="why-now-section">
    <h2>Service Terms</h2>
    <div class="why-now-grid">
      <div class="why-now-card">
        <h3>How AI Is Used in This Service</h3>
        <p>
          This research is produced with AI assistance. AI tools handle the heavy retrieval pass, source aggregation, and first-draft synthesis. A human (me) reviews every claim, verifies primary sources, applies professional judgment, structures the narrative, and signs off on the deliverable. You are paying for the judgment layer — the AI is in the basement, not the deliverable. This disclosure is provided in good faith and in alignment with FTC AI guidance and EU AI Act Article 50 transparency principles.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="why-now-card">
        <h3>What This Report Is — and Is Not</h3>
        <p>
          This is an informational market research deliverable produced for your internal decision-making. It is <strong>not</strong> legal advice, medical advice, financial advice, investment advice, or a regulatory submission. It is not a substitute for your own professional judgment, your own legal counsel, your own clinical expertise, or your own due diligence. You remain responsible for the decisions you make based on the report.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="why-now-card">
        <h3>Source Verification Commitment</h3>
        <p>
          Every factual claim in the report is cited to a primary source where one exists. You can independently verify any number, statistic, or assertion. If you find an error in citation or fact, tell me — I will correct and re-issue the report at no additional charge.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="why-now-card">
        <h3>Refund and Rework Policy</h3>
        <p>
          If the delivered report materially fails the scope agreed at intake — meaning what we agreed to research is not what was delivered — I will rework it at no additional charge or refund the full fee, your choice. This does not cover scope disagreements (you wanted a different angle, conclusion, or additional analysis). Those are handled as new engagements. The flat fee includes one round of clarification questions on the delivered report.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="why-now-card">
        <h3>Confidentiality and Data Handling</h3>
        <p>
          A mutual non-disclosure agreement is available on request before intake. Information you share is used only to produce your report and is not reused for other clients, not shared with third parties, and not used to train any AI model. Working files are retained for 90 days post-delivery for clarification purposes, then deleted unless you request earlier deletion.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="why-now-card">
        <h3>Independent Professional Capacity</h3>
        <p>
          This service is offered by Tyrian Murex in personal, independent capacity. It is not affiliated with, endorsed by, or representative of any employer or other institution. References to clinical research experience reflect Tyrian's professional background and do not imply institutional sponsorship of this work.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Base>
